modules.description: Tracks dynamic values that update in response to events, supporting reactive updates through event-driven logic. Operates on streams and signals, enabling real-time data flow management. Used to create interactive terminal interfaces by synchronizing user input with visual output.

Handles event-driven rendering by converting event streams into image streams for terminal output, using Lwt for asynchronous execution. Processes UI updates within Lwt threads, allowing event handlers to initiate and coordinate additional asynchronous operations. Operates on event streams, UI components defined as Lwd.t values, and produces Lwt-streams of terminal images.
